'application/zstd' Media Type
2021", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC8878.html", target="_top", tooltip="Zstandard, or zstd (pronounced zee standard), is a lossless data compression mechanism. This document describes the mechanism and registers a media type, content encoding, and a structured syntax suffix to be used when transporting zstd-compressed content via MIME. Despite use of the word standard as part of Zstandard, readers are advised that this document is not an Internet Standards Track specification; it is being published for informational purposes only. This document replaces and obsoletes RFC 8478."];
